---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import HeroSection from '../../components/home/HeroSection.astro';
import CoverStory from '../../components/home/CoverStory.astro';
import RandomDiscovery from '../../components/home/RandomDiscovery.astro';
import ReadingPath from '../../components/ReadingPath.astro';
import FeatureCards from '../../components/FeatureCards.astro';
import CategoriesSection from '../../components/home/CategoriesSection.astro';
import LanguageStatement from '../../components/home/LanguageStatement.astro';
import RecentUpdates from '../../components/home/RecentUpdates.astro';
import NewsletterSection from '../../components/home/NewsletterSection.astro';
import ContributeSection from '../../components/home/ContributeSection.astro';
import { fetchRecentCommits } from '../../lib/commits';

// 2026-04-25 β7 Phase 1：fix B2 (i18n-evolution-roadmap audit)
// 此頁面 prose 暫時使用英文（fr 跟 es FALLBACK_CHAIN 預設語言），
// 直到 community 提供 fr 翻譯 PR。Phase 2 結構同步後此檔將改為從
// shared homepage components import，不再各自獨立維護。

const recentCommits = await fetchRecentCommits();

const readingPathSteps = [
  {
    href: '/es/history/japanese-colonial-era',
    title: 'From Colony to Democracy: Taiwan’s History',
    description:
      'From authoritarianism to democracy: Asia’s first peaceful transition.',
    time: '6 min',
  },
  {
    href: '/es/culture/taiwan-religion-and-temple-culture',
    title: 'Plural Yet One: Taiwan’s Culture',
    description:
      'A vibrant cultural fabric woven by many ethnic groups together.',
    time: '7 min',
  },
  {
    href: '/es/food/night-market-culture',
    title: 'The Most Real Taste of Taiwan: Night Markets',
    description:
      'The world’s densest street-food and social space rolled into one.',
    time: '5 min',
  },
  {
    href: '/es/technology/semiconductor-industry',
    title: 'The Silicon Shield: Semiconductors',
    description:
      'How TSMC turned a small island into the heart of global tech.',
    time: '8 min',
  },
  {
    href: '/es/lifestyle/convenience-store-culture',
    title: 'The OS of Daily Life: Convenience Stores',
    description: 'Not just shops — they are the country’s infrastructure.',
    time: '4 min',
  },
];

const readingPathFooterItems = [
  { icon: '⏱️', label: '~30 minutes total' },
  { icon: '🎯', label: '5 core themes' },
  { icon: '🌟', label: 'A complete picture of Taiwan' },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Open-source knowledge base of Taiwan"
  description="An open-source, AI-friendly comprehensive knowledge base of Taiwan. 660+ articles spanning 12 themes — history, culture, food, music, technology and more — collaboratively curated by the community to introduce the real Taiwan to the world."
  lang="es"
>
  <HeroSection />

  <CoverStory />

  <RandomDiscovery />

  <ReadingPath
    lang="es"
    title="📖 Not sure where to start?"
    subtitle="Five articles, thirty minutes — and you’ll know the real Taiwan."
    steps={readingPathSteps}
    footerItems={readingPathFooterItems}
    continueHref="#categories"
    continueLabel="Explore more themes →"
  />

  <FeatureCards
    lang="es"
    sectionTitle="Why Taiwan.md?"
    cards={[
      {
        icon: '🎯',
        title: 'Curated, not encyclopedic',
        description:
          'Carefully curated, deep narratives — not encyclopedic enumerations.',
      },
      {
        icon: '🤖',
        title: 'AI-friendly by design',
        description:
          'Structured content so AI can also grasp Taiwan’s complexity.',
      },
      {
        icon: '🌍',
        title: 'Multilingual, international',
        description:
          'Starting from local perspectives, telling Taiwan’s story in international languages.',
      },
      {
        icon: '📚',
        title: 'Comprehensive and many-sided',
        description:
          '12+ thematic areas, presenting Taiwan as a three-dimensional whole.',
      },
    ]}
  />

  <CategoriesSection>
    <Fragment slot="prose">
      <p>
        This island is only 36,000 km², but it contains a microcosm of the
        world. From Yushan’s 3,952-meter peak to the Pacific’s deep trenches,
        <a href="/es/geography" class="topic-pill">🗺️ its geography</a>
        is orogeny live-streamed — plate collisions, volcanic eruptions, faulting,
        four million years of geological symphony shaping one of the youngest, most
        dynamic, most beautiful islands on Earth.
      </p>

      <p>
        Four hundred years ago, the Dutch built Fort Zeelandia in Tainan. Every
        regime since — Koxinga’s, the Qing, Japan, the KMT — left their mark on
        the island. But what truly made Taiwan, Taiwan, was the
        <a href="/es/history" class="topic-pill">📜 long awakening</a>
        from authoritarianism to democracy. From the blood and tears of 228 to the
        cheers when martial law lifted, from Formosa to Sunflower — every pain and
        resistance sharpened the island’s soul.
      </p>

      <p>
        Multiple bloodlines flow through this land. Indigenous peoples have
        lived here 6,000 years; Hoklo and Hakka came after the 17th century;
        mainlanders after WWII; new immigrants and migrant workers in recent
        decades — each bringing their language, faith and memory.
        <a href="/es/culture" class="topic-pill">🎭 Taiwan’s culture</a>
        is not a melting pot but a mosaic — every piece keeping its color and shape,
        together forming a picture seen nowhere else.
      </p>

      <p>
        Walk into any night market in Taiwan and you’ll smell oyster omelet from
        southern Fujian, Japanese tempura, and scallion pancakes brought by
        veterans from Shandong all in the same breath.
        <a href="/es/food" class="topic-pill">🍜 The flavors of this island</a>
        are migration history, written by the tongue. From street-stall warmth to
        Michelin precision, Taiwanese tell stories with food and preserve memory through
        cuisine.
      </p>

      <p>
        Calling Taiwan a butterfly kingdom is no romantic metaphor — it’s
        ecological fact. On an island smaller than the Netherlands live more
        than 59,000 species: 0.025% of Earth’s land area holding 2.5% of all
        known species.
        <a href="/es/nature" class="topic-pill">🌿 Taiwan’s nature</a>
        is a vertical textbook of evolution: tropical rainforest to alpine tundra,
        coral reefs to the Kuroshio current — species evolve, diverge, coexist. Yet
        industrial development has scarred the mountains and rivers; the tug-of-war
        between conservation and growth continues.
      </p>

      <p>
        From Lai He and Yang Kui to Pai Hsien-yung and Chu T’ien-hsin; from the
        Lin family of Wufeng to the Koo dynasty —
        <a href="/es/people" class="topic-pill">👥 Taiwan’s people</a>
        are the era in miniature. More than personal biographies, they are the collective
        memory of how this island survived in the cracks and found hope amid hardship.
        Behind every story: the resilience and choices of small individuals inside
        enormous times.
      </p>

      <p>
        From temple-fair eight-generals to contemporary art at the Venice
        Biennale,
        <a href="/es/art" class="topic-pill">🎨 Taiwan’s art</a>
        is dialogue between tradition and innovation. Cochin pottery and digital installation,
        traditional opera and experimental theater, indigenous totems and contemporary
        painting — artists keep asking: how do we respond with creation in this era?
        How do we preserve the local within globalization?
      </p>

      <p>
        From indigenous ancient ballads to Teng Yu-hsien’s &ldquo;Bāng
        Chhun-hong,&rdquo; from campus folk to the Golden Melody Awards,
        <a href="/es/music" class="topic-pill">🎵 Taiwan’s sound</a>
        is the island’s pulse. Music crosses ethnic, linguistic, and generational
        lines, becoming the most cohesive medium of collective memory. Mayday’s shouts
        at the Taipei Arena and indigenous elders chanting in their villages tell
        the same story: who we are and where we come from.
      </p>

      <p>
        TSMC’s wafers are not mere silicon chips; they are proof of Taiwan’s
        position on the global tech map.
        <a href="/es/technology" class="topic-pill">💻 This tech island</a>
        evolved from contract manufacturing to innovative R&D, from hardware advantage
        to software breakthroughs. But technology brings its own challenges: digital
        divide, AI substitution, cybersecurity threats — can Taiwan ride the tech
        wave without drowning?
      </p>

      <p>
        From Asian Tiger to semiconductor empire,
        <a href="/es/economy" class="topic-pill">📈 Taiwan’s economic miracle</a
        >
        is a textbook case of small-state grand strategy. But behind the miracle:
        countless overtime nights, granular cost control, unstopping pursuit of efficiency.
        Now facing the US-China trade war and global supply chain reshuffling, can
        Taiwan keep writing the legend?
      </p>

      <p>
        The keywords for
        <a href="/es/society" class="topic-pill">⚖️ Taiwan society</a>
        are diversity and inclusion. From Asia’s first marriage equality to ongoing
        transitional justice, from nuclear referendum to pension reform — Taiwanese
        are learning to dialogue inside opposition, to find consensus inside conflict.
        This is democracy’s practice ground; the laboratory of the future.
      </p>

      <p>
        Taiwanese
        <a href="/es/lifestyle" class="topic-pill">🏠 lifestyle</a>
        is convenience fused with human warmth. Convenience-store density is world-leading,
        yet night-market warmth remains one of a kind. Inside the 24-hour rhythm of
        the city, neighborhood greetings and care still endure. In the rush of globalization,
        how do Taiwanese keep their own life-philosophy? The answer is probably hidden
        in the everyday greeting: &ldquo;Have you eaten?&rdquo;
      </p>
    </Fragment>
  </CategoriesSection>

  <LanguageStatement />

  <RecentUpdates commits={recentCommits} />

  <NewsletterSection />

  <ContributeSection />
</Layout>
